-- ChelPipe Surges 30%, Most in 3 Years, on Deal Announcement
-- B y   L y u b o v   P r o n i n a
-- 2012-09-24T16:59:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/chelpipe-surges-30-most-in-3-years-on-deal-announcement.html
 ChelPipe surged the most in more
than three years as the Russian pipemaker announced a deal
involving company property worth more than 50% of the value of
its assets.
* ChelPipe, controlled by Andrey Komarov, surged 30%, the most
since May 28, 2009, and closed at 38.09 rubles in Moscow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lyubov Pronina in London at 
